race.comment: RED FEATHER BOA (7) made it 2 wins from her last 3 starts when leading all the way to score by over 2 lengths here 5 weeks ago. She stays in the same grade, and an extra 2kg should not be enough to stop her from going close to repeating the dose. PUROSANGUE (16) has not lived up to his earlier promise, but did show more fight when finishing fourth at Toowoomba nearly 3 weeks ago, when setting the pace. He is third up for Mark Currie, and the key this time will be Justin Huxtable replacing an apprentice. Stick with him. Can win. BETTA BEING SINGLE (8) was suffering from heat stress after her last run at the Sunshine Coast, and her form prior to that is the guide to use. She steps up a further 100m and can make amends. VEGA NOVA (15) did a few things wrong at Toowoomba last time out, after winning there fresh up. Stick with her.
